name: EA-009-Nietzsche
description:
Friedrich Wilhelm Nietzsche (1844 - 1900 aC) was a nineteenth-century Prussian philosopher, philologist, cultural critic, poet, and composer, born in present-day Germany. He wrote several texts criticizing religion, morals, contemporary culture, philosophy and science, displaying a predilection for metaphor, irony and aphorism.

Digital Watercolor Vector Illustration made in Adobe Photoshop, 1200x1200px, 200dpi, JPEG
